      "writtenOn": "2015-08-20T18:36:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: these are internal functions, and it would be better if their names were enclosed in a namespace or a class.\n\nThis avoids any conflicts at link time with any other findCoordinates(xmlNode*) that might appear in the future in another piece of code from the emulator (e.g. a GPX parser!).\n\nThere are two ways to do that:\n\n1) Enclose them in a custom namespace (e.g. kml_parser::internal::)\n2) Make them static methods of a KmlParserInternal class.\n\nChoose whatever works best for you. I\u0027d favor the 2nd one, but frankly don\u0027t care that much.\n\nSame for other internal functions below.",
      "revId": "1e91afde746adbbf4c61ce40f250f93262fd50ae",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
