      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: this name is too generic, either enclosing it a namespace (e.g. android::kml) or define it as a static method in a class, as in:\n\n  class KmlParser {\n  public:\n    static bool parseFile(...);\n  };\n\nThis way, the function name will be KmlParser::parseFile().\n\nI recommend this approach and put the definitions of GpsFix and GpsFixArray into the same class (so their names will be KmlParser::GpsFix and KmlParser::GpsFixArray).",
